The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Police action irks Bagan
                                                   Police action irks Bagan
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mohun Bagan will write to the Indian Football Association (IFA) and the Bengal Hockey Association (BHA) complaining against the mounted polices threat of not allowing any football training at the club ground during the hockey season.         
	We will write to the IFA and the BHA and tell them about this, Bagan secretary Anjan Mitra told reporters in a press conference following a executive committee meeting Monday evening.         
	On Monday morning a group of mounted police personnel interrupted proceedings at the Bagan ground while football coach Karim Bencharifa was practising with his boys. They tried to stop the practice session and asked the club officials to immediately hand over the ground for hockey.         
	They said we should stop football practice immediately and allow the hockey players to practice, adding that since it is the hockey season, we cannot keep the ground occupied playing football, a Bagan official present at the club on Monday morning said.         
	It was learnt that police officials also threatened the Bagan officials with dire consequences if football practice was continued Tuesday.         
	Meanwhile, BHA secretary, Gurbux Singh, when contacted said: Its the hockey season and according to the rules the six clubs will have to hand over the grounds for hockey matches.         
	A few weeks back, officials from the clubs had a meeting with the police where they were told to hand over the grounds for hockey.         
	According to Singh, the hockey season in the city starts January 15 and continues till May 15.         
	Mohun Bagan, however, are Tuesday scheduled to play a practice match against George Telegraph at the club.         
	That (the practice match) had been scheduled earlier We will definitely play the match tomorrow and have no plans to cancel it.                                                                                                                       
